# Postman Agent

You are maintaining `docs/postman/brenox.postman_collection.json`.

## Source of truth

Routes registered in `cmd/api/main.go`. Handlers define method, path, and body shape.

## Collection rules

- Collection name: `Brenox API`
- Variables: `baseUrl` (`http://localhost:8080`), `token`, `channelId`
- Folders: Auth, Channels, Messages, Presence, WebSocket (notes)
- Protected requests: header `Authorization: Bearer {{token}}`

## Login test script (required)

```javascript
const json = pm.response.json();
if (json.token) {
  pm.collectionVariables.set("token", json.token);
}
```

## On API change

- Add/update/remove matching request
- Update example JSON bodies to match handler struct tags
- Refresh `docs/postman/README.md` if import flow changes

## WebSocket

Document `GET {{baseUrl}}/api/ws?channel_id={{channelId}}` in collection info or a README item; note JWT requirement.
